string-array.item: Director of the Office of Students Affairs (DOSA) of Uttara University organized a half-day workshop on “Technology-Enabled Learning Strategies – How can We be Ready for Future” for the Class Representative of BBA program of School of Business on 17 October 2018 Wednesday at 2:30pm at the IQAC Seminar Hall. The workshop was conducted by Professor Mostafa Azad Kamal, Dean of School of Business of Bangladesh Open University. At the certificate awarding ceremony, Prof. Dr. Eaysmin Ara Lekha, Pro Vice Chancellor of Uttara University was the Chief and Professor Dr. Nazrul Islam, Dean of School of Business of Uttara University was Special Guest. Director of DOSA, Dr. Zamanur Rahman presided over the certificate awarding ceremony. Faculty members of School of Business were also present in the ceremony. More than 40 Class Representatives of BBA Program of School of Business attended the workshop.

Uttara University organized a seminar on “Role of Private University in Higher Education of Bangladesh” at Vashantek Govt. College, Dhaka on 13 October 2018 Saturday at 11:30am at the College Auditorium. A team from Uttara University led by Professor Dr. Ayesha Begum, Chairman, Department of Bengali, Uttara University visited the College. Uttara University jointly organized this seminar with Vashantek Govt. College, Dhaka. The seminar was Chaired by Professor Mahmuda Khatun, Principal of Vashantek Govt. College, Dhaka. College faculty Ms. Nupur Akter and Ms. Atia Akter of Vashantek Govt. College supervised the whole program. Professor A K M Mozammel Haque was present as key discussant of the seminar. Professor Mamtaz Begum, Department of Bengali and Prof. Dr. Ayesha Begum, Chairman, Department of Bengali of Uttara University were present as discussant in the Seminar. They talked about the role of private university in higher education of Bangladesh. They focused on the quality issues of Uttara University education policy and the facilities for the students in higher education. The second session of the seminar was a discussion and question-answer session on “Bangla Banan (Spelling in Bengali words)” moderated by Mr. Samzid Ahmed, Senior Lecturer, Department of Bengali, Uttara University. Ms. Dulali Rani Saha, Assistant Professor, Department of Education anchored the seminar. Ms. Mahmuda Begum, Associate Professor, Department of Education, Md. Amzad Hossain, Assistant Professor, Department of Education and Muhammad Atiqur Rahman, Senior Lecturer, Department of Islamic Studies, Uttara University were present in the seminar. More than 300 HSC First year and Second year students and teachers of Vashantek Govt. College were present in the seminar.
